name: Squat
description: A squat is a strength exercise in which the trainee lowers their hips from a standing position and then stands back up.

name: Bridge
description: Do the bridge to strengthen your core muscles. Lie on your back with your knees bent. Raise your hips off the floor until your hips are aligned with your knees.

name: pushup
description: a conditioning exercise performed in a prone position by raising and lowering the body with the straightening .

name: Lunges
description: A lunge can refer to any position of the human body where one leg is positioned forward with knee bent .

name: Standing overhead dumbbell presses
description: The way to do the overhead dumbbell press is to master the start and end positions find the bottom of rack position by holding a pair of dumbbells.

name: Single-leg deadlifts
description: This is another exercise that challenges your balance. Single-leg deadlifts require stability and leg strength. Grab a light to moderate dumbbell to complete this move.
